Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9x9-inch baking dish. Place the stuffing mix into a bowl, and thoroughly mix in the minced oysters, chicken broth, margarine, and sage. Spoon the stuffing into the prepared baking dish, and cover dish with foil. Bake in the preheated oven until the stuffing is thoroughly heated through, 30 to 40 minutes.